status: MARC21-007: Color characteristics of a projected graphic
Color characteristics of a projected graphic.

definition (en): Image is printed or executed in a single color (i.e., monochromatic).
scope note (en): Used only for transparency sets. Does not include black.

definition (en): Image is printed or executed in black-and-white. Refers to monochrome photographic materials (including film) and videorecordings, or to overhead transparencies executed in black-and-white.
scope note (en): Does not include tinted, toned, or stained items.

definition (en): Image is printed or executed in more than one color. The color is a result of a number of processes, either photographic or electronic, capable of reproducing a reasonable range of hues, or of original application of color materials, for example, paint.
scope note (en): Used for color photographic processes (motion pictures, filmstrips, transparencies, and slides), color videorecordings, or multicolored overhead transparencies.

definition (en): Image, produced by a printing or photographic process, is hand colored.
A combination of one color, black and white, colored, hand colored, and/or other images.

scope note (en): For example, when the item in hand is sound track film intended to accompany visual images not actually present.

definition (en): Color characteristics of the projected graphic are not known.
Color other than one color, black-and-white, multicolored, hand colored, mixed.
